latestPosts.caption:
To my dearest Dadda,

No matter how much I write about you, no words could ever truly capture how incredible you are. You are the best human being I’ve ever known. While the world might not see all of you, I know the depth of your kindness, the warmth of your heart, and the way your smile lights up everything around you.

Since the day you left us, the world has thrown its comments, opinions, and hurtful words my way. But you know the drill: “Kuch toh log kahenge, logon ka kaam hai kehna.” I promise to rise above it all and become the best version of myself—for you.

I miss so much about you—my biryani partner who always knows how to cheer me up, my chef, my vibey, my best friend, my biggest cheerleader and my partner-in-crime.

You have a heart that feels deeply for others, one that is filled with nothing but love for your family. You’ve given us more love than we could ever ask for, a love so pure that no one else could ever match it.

Dadda, you’re my superstar, my most precious person. I live for you, for our dreams, and for everything you are. I promise to make you proud—I will never fail in that. One day, the world will say, “Aval Renchy de mol aa.”

You’ve taught me to be strong, to rise above pain, and to keep striving, no matter what. I know you already see that strength in me.

Life has always been unfair to me, but the greatest and most painful truth is that Dadda Girija and Kunju didn’t deserve this end.

But even through the pain, I will rise, just as you taught me. I’ll carry your legacy of love, strength, and kindness, always

With all my love,
Kunju, Kochu, Kuku, Riyeee, Dadda’s Molluuu
